article.description: Boston U. 86, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 77
article.headline: Boston U. 86, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 77
article.linkText: Boston U. 86, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 77
article.story: BOSTON -- Jake O'Brien and John Holland each scored 21 points, and Boston University beat Mount St. Mary's (Md.) 86-77 on Tuesday night. Holland, who made 6 of 11 field goals and was 9-for-13 from the foul line, has scored in double figures in 29 straight games. Tyler Morris added 17 points and Corey Lowe had 13 for the Terriers (5-6), who have won three games in a row. The Terriers shot 56 percent from the field (28 of 50). The Terriers built their biggest lead at 63-44 with 10:08 to play on a pair of free throws by O'Brien. The Mountaineers (3-8) would get no closer than the final margin the rest of the way. Mount St. Mary's closed the game on an 8-2 run. Jeremy Goode led the Mountaineers, who lost their sixth straight game, with 20 points. Kelly Beidler added 17 points, Jean Cajou had 16 and Will Holland 13.
